Modelo inicial

m1 <- inla(redundancy ~
             longitude +
             latitude  +
             sand      +
             limo      +
             clay      +
             p_h       +
             acidity   +
             ca        +
             mg        +
             k         +
             p         +
             organic_matter +
             elev      +
             prec       +
             precdriest +
             preccv     +
             temp      +
             tempmin,
             
          family = "gaussian",
          
          control.compute = list(
                               dic = TRUE,
                               waic = TRUE),
          control.predictor = list(compute = TRUE),
          data = dredundancy_eff)


lm <- lm(dredundancy_eff$redundancy ~
                          pca_envi$x[,1] +
                          pca_envi$x[,2] +
                          pca_envi$x[,3])




pca_regresssion <- inla(redundancy ~
                          pca_envi$x[,1] +
                          pca_envi$x[,2] +
                          pca_envi$x[,3],
                          
                        family = "gaussian",
          
          control.compute = list(
                               dic = TRUE,
                               waic = TRUE),
          control.predictor = list(compute = TRUE),
          data = dredundancy_eff 
          )

#Pearson residuals
ExpY <- pca_regresssion$summary.fitted.values[,"mean"]
E1   <- (dredundancy_eff$redundancy - ExpY) / sqrt(ExpY)
dredundancy_eff$E1 <- E1

Spatial dependency in the Pearson residuals

dredundancy_eff$crtm_90_x <- dredundancy_eff$crtm_90_x/1000 
dredundancy_eff$crtm_90_y <- dredundancy_eff$crtm_90_y/1000 
# Sample-variogram with distances up to 100 km
vario_data <- data.frame( E1 = E1, 
                          Xkm = dredundancy_eff$crtm_90_x, 
                          Ykm = dredundancy_eff$crtm_90_y)
coordinates(vario_data)    <- c("Xkm", "Ykm")
vario <- variogram( object = E1 ~ Xkm + Ykm , 
                    data = vario_data, 
                    cressie = TRUE, 
                    cutoff = 10,
                    width = 0.2)

p <- ggplot(data = vario, aes(x = dist, y = gamma))
p <- p + geom_point()
p <- p + geom_smooth(method = "gam", 
                     formula = y ~ s(x, bs = "cs"),
                     colour = "black") 
#p <- p + ylim(0,1)
p <- p + theme(text = element_text(size = 15)) 
p <- p + xlab("Distance (km)") + ylab("Sample variogram") 
p
